Management of the Niger State-owned University, Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida University Lapai (IBBUL) announced the death of the Deputy Vice-Chancellor, Administration, Professor Mohammed Saba Mohammed after a brief illness. According to a statement issued by the Registrar of the university, Mallam M A Abdullahi, and made available to Journalists on Monday in Minna, the deceased Prof S A Mohammed was a Professor of Sports Psychology. The statement added that the late DVC, Administration, was a hard-working academic staff whose contributions to the growth of the university were immeasurable. The Registrar thereby prayed that may the soul of the departed University Administrator rest in peace and may the Almighty Allah give the family the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss. Meanwhile, the Jana’iza prayers of late Prof. Mohammed Saba Mohammed will take place at his residence in Tunga behind Dogon Koli Hotel adjacent NNPC Mega station, Minna. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state… Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report… [ICYMI] Lekki Shootings: Why We Lied About Our Presence — General Taiwo The Lagos State Judicial Panel of Inquiry probing the killings at Lekki Toll Gate, on Saturday resumed viewing of the 24hrs footage of the Octo